Employer: The Hotel Association of Los Angeles
Address: 900 Wilshire Blvd; 506 South Grand Ave; 900 West Olympic Blvd; 101 Wilshire Blvd; 9750 Airport Blvd; 9901 S La Cienega Blvd; 2100 E Mariposa Ave; 1855 S Harbor Blvd
City: Los Angeles; Los Angeles; Los Angeles; Santa Monica; Los Angeles; Los Angeles; El Segundo; Anaheim
Worker Demands: Pay, Healthcare, Racial justice, Staffing, Retirement benefits, Create a fund to assist workers in obtaining affordable housing; Demand permanent jobs for replacement workers
Notes: As part of a series of rolling strikes regarding a contract covering 60 hotels in Southern California, on July 2, 2023, 15,000 workers across 21 hotels went on strike for 3 days. In the second wave of strikes, on July 10, 2023, 3,200 workers across 12 hotels went on strike for 5 days. In the third wave of strikes, on July 20, 2023, 1,750 workers across 8 hotels went on strike. In the fourth wave of strikes, on August 3, 2023, 1,000 workers across 26 hotels went on strike for 5 days. In the fifth wave of strikes, on August 30, 2023, 3,150 workers across 13 hotels went on strike. In the sixth wave of strikes, on September 25, 2023, 1,000 workers across 8 hotels went on strike. In the seventh wave of strikes, on October 6, 2023, workers across 9 hotels went on strike. In the eighth wave of strikes, on October 25, 2023, workers across 50 hotels went on strike. In the ninth wave of strikes, on November 1, 2023, workers across Santa Monica hotels went on strike. On November 17, 2023, workers at the Hilton Anaheim walked out on strike. On December 13, 2023, workers at the Sheraton Park Hotel at the Anaheim Resort walked out on strike. In the tenth wave of strikes, on December 17, 2023, workers across 6 hotels indefinitely went on strike. On December 31, 2023, workers at 2 Pasadena hotels went on strike for 2 days. We list 8 of the locations where workers have gone on strike during this contract campaign.

Notes: A "walk-in" protest was held on the morning of the picket at 30 schools across the district.

From January 17, 2024 to January 19th, 2024, bus drivers and classified staff held a sickout. On January 31st, 12 schools were shut down due to an employee and teacher sickout. On February 5th, 7 schools were shut down to an employee and teacher sickout. On February 9th, the entire transportation department and other teachers and staff called out sick, forcing the district to cancel classes district-wide. Not all of these workers are covered by the Durham Education Association. Instead of listing all schools involved in these strikes, we list the office for the Durham Public Schools Board of Education.
